-- LME Copper Futures Gain 0.4% to $6,709 a Metric Ton, Rise for Seventh Day
-- Glenys Sim
-- 2010-06-16T00:05:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-16/lme-copper-futures-gain-0-4-to-6-709-a-metric-ton-rise-for-seventh-day.html

          
          
             Three-month copper futures on the
London Metal Exchange gained as much as 0.4 percent to $6,709 a
metric ton, advancing for a seventh straight day. Nickel, zinc
and aluminum futures also climbed.  
